# Accessibility

## Tree View (W3C TreeView Pattern)

Tree components must follow the WAI-ARIA TreeView pattern:

- Container: `role="tree"` with `aria-label`
- Each row: `role="treeitem"` with `aria-level`, `aria-posinset`, `aria-setsize`
- Container nodes: `aria-expanded="true"` or `"false"`
- Selected node: `aria-selected="true"`
- Nested groups: `role="group"`

Keyboard navigation (roving tabindex):
- `↑`/`↓`: Navigate between visible nodes
- `←`: Collapse current or move to parent
- `→`: Expand current or move to first child
- `Home`/`End`: First/last visible node
- `Enter`: Select focused node

Only one treeitem has `tabindex="0"` at a time; all others get `tabindex="-1"`.

## Color Contrast

All text must meet WCAG AA: 4.5:1 ratio for body text, 3:1 for large text (18px+).
Don't rely on color alone to convey type — add secondary indicators (quotes, italic, icons).

## Interactive Elements

- All buttons need `aria-label` or visible text
- Modals need focus trapping and `Escape` to close
- Visible focus indicators on all interactive elements (`ring-2`)
- Tables need `aria-sort` on sortable column headers
